						               													<description>Crosswords is a word game in the spirit of Scrabble, on a unique grid and with some options that make it a different (and more interesting) game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The board is an octagon-diamond grid, where the octagons hold the letters, and randomly selected intermediate diamonds indicate letter or word bonuses.  &amp;#10;     Bonuses not always in the same places, and score for each letter placed adjacent to them.&amp;#10;     Octagons instead of squares, allow diagonal words to be visualized..&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Words can be restricted to the traditional horizontal and vertical directions, or diagonal words can be allowed.  Other options include playing &amp;quot;backwards&amp;quot; words, and playing multiple connected words at once.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All combined, Crosswords is a lot more varied and strategic than Scrabble.  The variable&amp;#10;number and position of the bonuses, and the multiple use of bonuses, makes play a lot more&amp;#10;variable.    Likewise, allowing backwards and diagonal words unclogs the grid, which can&amp;#10;expand in any direction.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
